#######################################################################################################
Very small and simple writeup:
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
--used a very long extensive string with the profile name. (AAs or 0x41s)
--Crashed and overwritten $ra and other stack registers
--Refined the PoC to stop crashing at 0x41414141.
--Find payload address
--Look for the game's SDK. I choose `sceKernalExitGame` since every PSP game should have one
--Pasted the offset into my save with the appropriate little endian address.
--Worked and I pasted the color flasher payload
--Done
########################################################################################################

0x33 = $ra control's offset in savegame
0xE0 = PoC Payload Offset

0x08000000 + 0x00CEAD78 = 0x08CEAD78: payload address

Simple PSP SDK Calls:
0x088C3798 = sceKernelExitGame /* SDK that was used to initial test my exploit */
